<div id="review_714559805" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/714559805" />
    <a title="Charles Ameringer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16937713-charles-ameringer"><img alt="Charles Ameringer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1454601846p2/16937713.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/714559805?book_show_action=true">Sep 08, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charles Ameringer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charles Ameringer" href="/user/show/16937713-charles-ameringer">Charles Ameringer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16937713-charles-ameringer?shelf=havana-queen">havana-queen</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer714559805" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8562981321023578939">HAVANA QUEEN is one of the best political/espionage novels that I have ever read. James Bruno has combined superb literary skills with a remarkable breadth of knowledge to produce a tale of spy derring-do and political upheaval set in Cuba today and possibly tomorrow. He supports a jam-packed story of adventure and intrigue with vivid descriptions of political and living conditions inside contemporary Cuba, along with a virtual textbook of CIA tradecraft and FBI sleuthing. Weaving multiple story</span>
  <span id="freeText8562981321023578939" style="display:none">HAVANA QUEEN is one of the best political/espionage novels that I have ever read. James Bruno has combined superb literary skills with a remarkable breadth of knowledge to produce a tale of spy derring-do and political upheaval set in Cuba today and possibly tomorrow. He supports a jam-packed story of adventure and intrigue with vivid descriptions of political and living conditions inside contemporary Cuba, along with a virtual textbook of CIA tradecraft and FBI sleuthing. Weaving multiple story lines, Mr. Bruno creates a tapestry of intricate design that includes guerrilla operations in the Sierra Maestra, the water boarding of his hero Nick Castillo, and the ferreting out of moles in the State Department and Defense Intelligence Agency. If he's at all prophetic, the Castro brothers are in deep trouble. As a former diplomat and military intelligence analyst, Mr. Bruno provides a wealth of insider information that is breath-taking in its revelations. It's amazing that he got the green light from the security review process. HAVANA QUEEN is a book that you can't put down and which you hate to see come to an end. It is a most enjoyable and captivating reading experience. I give it five stars plus.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8562981321023578939" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


