        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer897041300" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18070549024135757913">BRUNO SCORES AGAIN! Havana Queen is a fast paced, action filled adventure centered on the never ending battle between intelligence and counterintelligence forces of opposed political ideologies. Immerse yourself in the decades long battle between the United States and Fidel Castro’s Cuba in the persons of the US Federal Bureau of Investigation’s Nick Castillo, the son of Cuban immigrant refugees, Colonel Henrique Marcial Arribe, a Cuban Frontier Brigade commander, Kate Kovalchuk, a US Central In</span>
  <span id="freeText18070549024135757913" style="display:none">BRUNO SCORES AGAIN! Havana Queen is a fast paced, action filled adventure centered on the never ending battle between intelligence and counterintelligence forces of opposed political ideologies. Immerse yourself in the decades long battle between the United States and Fidel Castro’s Cuba in the persons of the US Federal Bureau of Investigation’s Nick Castillo, the son of Cuban immigrant refugees, Colonel Henrique Marcial Arribe, a Cuban Frontier Brigade commander, Kate Kovalchuk, a US Central Intelligence Analyst, and Larisa Montilla, a Cuban intelligence/counterintelligence officer and member of the Castro’s inner circle. Field agents meet violent ends or are “turned”; counter-moves and ultra-secret plots are launched; lust, love, and betrayal play their roles; a revolution is born and prosecuted in which the outcome is less than certain; and MORE. Rooting for the “good guys” is breath-shortening because you can never be sure of who is and who isn’t. James Bruno kept me engaged … no doubt. I encourage you to join me as a James Bruno fan.<br /><br /></span>
