<span id="freeTextContainer9156469430561553215">This is not just another spy novel - it&apos;s much more! It has the requisite male FBI agent, Nick Castillo, who was born in the US to Cuban immigrants, along with the requisite love interests, and a plot where good conquers evil. What differentiates it from the norm is an intricately-woven plot. Characters are introduced in vignettes, then a few chapters later begin the weaving process. Just when you think the story is about to reach its conclusion, another loose thread is brought in. The author&apos;s </span>
  <span id="freeText9156469430561553215" style="display:none">This is not just another spy novel - it's much more! It has the requisite male FBI agent, Nick Castillo, who was born in the US to Cuban immigrants, along with the requisite love interests, and a plot where good conquers evil. What differentiates it from the norm is an intricately-woven plot. Characters are introduced in vignettes, then a few chapters later begin the weaving process. Just when you think the story is about to reach its conclusion, another loose thread is brought in. The author's subject knowledge and the hopeful picture he paints for cuba make this a wonderful read!<br /><br />I received this book in a LibraryThing giveaway.</span>
