<span id="freeTextContainer16435179831545816183">Havana Queen kept me engaged. Until the last third that is, when the protagonists&apos; actions become plain unbelievable. The plot is good as is Mr. Bruno’s knowledge of the Cuban situation. However, the characters are so weak and their motives are so unjustified! Mr. Bruno has all the right stuff, a good editor would have tweaked his protagonists.<br/>He CAN write and that is the damn shame. </span>
